This paper is about a method for improving sequence generation using lexical constraints. The paper specifically focuses on experiments in neural machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). However, the method presented in the paper is general and can be applied to any model that generates a sequence, which could also fall under categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), or cs.CV (Computer Vision).
